  "prompt": "Why isn't hockey the national game of India?",
  "response": "While hockey has a rich history in India, including numerous achievements and widespread popularity, it is not officially designated as the national game. There isn't a formal declaration naming any sport as the national game of India.\n\nIn recent years, cricket has become exceptionally popular and influential in the country, often overshadowing other sports, including hockey. Despite this, both cricket and hockey, along with a variety of other sports, play a significant role in India's sporting culture. It's important to note that the concept of a \"national game\" can be more symbolic and may not necessarily require formal government recognition.",
